# Col du Sofa

Two sustained climbs that simulate long mountain passes. Power ramps up gradually as the road tilts skyward. Stay seated, drop your cadence, grip the bars and grind. The summit is up there somewhere.

- 10:00 45%
  - :30 Easy warmup — enjoy the valley while you can
  - 5:00 Loosen up the legs, you'll need them
  - 3:00 First climb starts in 2 minutes — drop your cadence to 70-75rpm
  - :30 The road is tilting up
- 20:00 80%..95% 70rpm
  - :30 The climb begins — start steady, don't burn your matches early
  - 5:00 The gradient is increasing, power will creep up naturally
  - 5:00 Halfway up — stay seated and grind, smooth circles
  - 5:00 The summit is getting closer — don't crack now
  - 3:00 Almost there — 2 minutes to the top, keep your head down
  - 1:00 The summit! Push over the top
- 5:00 45%
  - :10 Over the crest! Enjoy the descent
  - 3:00 Spin easy — the second climb starts in 2 minutes
  - 1:00 This one's steeper but shorter
- 15:00 85%..100% 65rpm
  - :30 Here we go again — steeper from the start
  - 4:00 Keep the cadence low and steady, let the gears do the work
  - 4:00 Halfway — you know this pain, you've been here before
  - 3:00 3 minutes to the summit — dig into your reserves
  - 2:00 The hairpin bends are behind you — just the final ramp
  - :30 SUMMIT! You made it!
- 10:00 40%
  - :10 Descend all the way home
  - 5:00 Easy spinning — great climbing today
